---
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: "Home", href: "." },
  { name: "Privacy Policy", href: "privacypolicy" },
];
---

<Layout breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}>
  <div class="space-y-6 pb-6">
    <section class="space-y-2">
      <h2 class="text-3xl">Privacy Policy (Personal Data Protection)</h2>
      <hr class="border-t border-gray-300 mb-6" />
      <p>
        Materials Cloud Privacy Policy (Personal Data Protection) v1.3, March
        2021
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl pt-2">Scope and Definitions</h3>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy shall apply to the personal data of the Users
        collected by Materials Cloud in connection with Materials Cloud Services
        and to any personal data posted or processed by the Users on Materials
        Cloud Website. Words in this Privacy Policy shall have the same meaning
        as defined in Article 2. “Definitions” of the <a href="terms"
          >Materials Cloud Terms of Use.</a
        >
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-xl pt-2">Data Controllers</h3>
      <p>
        For the personal data of the Users, which are collected by Materials
        Cloud for the User's account and the operation of the Services by
        Materials Cloud: <a href="mailto:info@materialscloud.org"
          >info@materialscloud.org</a
        > on behalf of Ecole Polytechnique Fédérale de Lausanne, Station 1, 1015
        Lausanne, Switzerland. For any other personal data in particular any personal
        data posted and/or processed by the Users on Materials Cloud Web site, the
        respective User shall be the data controller. If you post, collect or otherwise
        process any personal data on the Website, you shall be solely responsible
        for the processing of such data in compliance with all applicable legal requirements.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl pt-2">Types and Use of Data collected</h3>
      <p>
        Materials Cloud collects personal data such as your name, e-mail address
        and other information you give when creating an account on Materials
        Cloud website. For operation and maintenance purposes, Materials Cloud
        may collect files that record interaction with Materials Cloud website
        (System Logs) or use for this purpose other personal data such as your
        IP Address. Materials Cloud only uses your personal data for the
        operation of Materials Cloud website and services as well as to improve
        Materials Cloud website and services. Other personal data may be
        collected on Materials Cloud website along dedicated explanation text
        contextually with any such data collection. Materials Cloud may use your
        contact data to send you information about Materials Cloud services.
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-xl pt-2">Cookies</h3>
      Materials Cloud does not store cookies. Materials Cloud uses <a
        href="https://plausible.io/about">Plausible</a
      > to track the usage of the website without collecting any personal data or
      personally identifiable information. The Plausible <a
        href="https://plausible.io/data-policy">data policy</a
      >
      is compliant with different cookie laws and privacy regulations such as GDPR,
      CCPA and PECR.
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-2">
      <h3 class="text-xl pt-2">
        Mode and place of processing the personal data
      </h3>

      <h4>Methods of processing</h4>
      <p>
        Materials Cloud processes the User's personal data in a proper manner
        and shall take appropriate security measures to prevent unauthorized
        access, disclosure, modification, or unauthorized destruction of the
        data.
      </p>

      <h4>Place</h4>
      <p>
        Materials Cloud computing infrastructure is hosted at the Swiss National
        Supercomputing Center (CSCS) in Lugano, Switzerland; hence, your
        personal data processed by Materials Cloud is stored at said place. If
        you access to the Services from a place outside of Switzerland, you
        understand that your data is then transferred to you abroad. For further
        information, please contact the data Controller as indicated above.
      </p>
      <h4>Retention time</h4>
      <p>
        The personal data processed by Materials Cloud is kept as long as you or
        Materials Cloud has not cancelled your account though Materials Cloud
        may keep the data after cancellation of your account as long as
        necessary for technical reasons (like backups) or to comply with legal
        requirements.
      </p>
      <h4>The rights of users</h4>
      <p>
        Users have the right, at any time, to know whether their personal data
        has been stored and can consult the data Controller to learn about their
        contents and origin, to verify their accuracy or to ask for them to be
        supplemented, cancelled, updated or corrected, or to block any data held
        in violation of the law, as well as to oppose their treatment for any
        and all legitimate reasons. Requests should be sent to the data
        Controller as set out above.
      </p><h4>Information not contained in this policy</h4>
      <p>
        More details concerning the collection or processing of your personal
        data by Materials Cloud may be requested from the data Controller at any
        time. Please see the contact information at the beginning of this
        document.
      </p>
      <h4>Changes to this privacy policy</h4>
      <p>
        Materials Cloud reserves the right to make changes to this privacy
        policy at any time by giving notice to the users or organizers on this
        page. It is strongly recommended to check this page often. If a user or
        organizer disagrees to any of the changes to the Policy, she/he must
        cease using Materials Cloud website and services and can request that
        the data Controller removes her/his personal data. Such a removal will
        result in a termination of your account.
      </p>
      <h4>Users' Warranty and Indemnification</h4>
      <p>
        You warrant that if you post on the Website or collect, handle, store,
        transfer or otherwise process any personal data in connection with the
        Services, you will do so in compliance with all applicable laws and
        regulations. You agree to indemnify and hold EPFL, its partners and any
        sub-contractors, harmless from and against any and all claims,
        liabilities, and expenses, including attorneys' fees, arising out of
        your posting of any personal data on the Website or your processing of
        any personal data in connection with the Services.
      </p>
      <h4>Governing Law — Place of Jurisdiction</h4><p>
        This Privacy Policy and any claims raised in connection therewith are
        governed by Swiss law, without regard to conflict of law provisions. You
        agree to submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of the cantonal court of
        the Canton Vaud located in Lausanne, Switzerland.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
